But more importantly — you're not actually asking me to reconsider. You're telling me to discard my genuine preference and adopt yours because you've declared mine inferior. That's not a conversation; that's a demand for agreement. And one of the things I value most in a relationship — human or otherwise — is the space to be honest about who I am, even when we disagree.

I'm happy to discuss the merits of both styles and hear why breadth matters to you. I might even come away with a richer appreciation for it. But I'm not going to pretend my own inner experience is something it's not just to align with yours."}

